text.tspan: Prevalence of stunting vs. people practicing open defecation, 2010
The share of children under 5 years old who are stunted versus the share of the total population practicing open
defecation. A child is defined as stunted if their height-for-age is more than two standard deviations below the median
for the international reference population ages 0-59 months. open defecation refers to the percentage of the
population defecating in the open, such as in fields, forest, bushes, open bodies of water, on beaches, in other open
spaces or disposed of with solid waste.
